10:07 AM; Case called for Bail/bond hearing.  Prosecuting attorney Andrea M Will in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Danielle L Krueger in court.  Attorney Bradley W Novreske in court for Danielle L Krueger. Court notes that Judge Melvin, who this case is assigned to, requested another branch hear this matter to address the issue regarding defendant's passport.  Atty. Novreske confirms and notes he filed a letter stating that his client looked and could not find her passport so she had it canceled.  State takes no position with respect to the issue.  Atty. Novereske just requests that the court amend the bail conditions to state that the defendant may not obtain a new passport without Court's approval.  Court will order the conditions of bond be amended to state that the Defendant may not obtain a new passport without approval from the Court and will remove the condition that the defendant must turn in her passport; all other conditions to remain as previously set.  Court inquires if there is another court date before Branch 5.  Counsel advises there are no future court dates.  Court will adjourn for continued status back before Branch 5 in about 30-45 days.  Hearing scheduled for October 27, 2022 at 09:30 am.
